The paper deals with network centrality and network design, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the influence of central nodes in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC). Additionally, the paper proposes a greedy algorithm and an efficient sampling algorithm, which are techniques that are commonly used in the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
